name: lib/Avatar.js

params.name: props.icon
params.description: Icon name

params.name: props.src
params.description: Image src

params.name: props.size
params.description: Avatar size

params.name: props.color
params.description: Color of icon of Avatar. Accept a color string such as RGBA,RGB,HEX.

params.name: props.primaryColor
params.description:
Background color of Avatar. Only use with a icon prop.
Accept a color string such as RGBA,RGB,HEX.

name: lib/Button.js
Button

params.name: props.value
params.description: Button Text. If language is english, all letters should be capitalized.

params.name: props.disabled
params.description: if `true`, Button can't be pressed

params.name: props.theme
params.description: Button Theme

params.name: props.primary
params.description: Primary color name

params.name: props.raised
params.description: Whether Button looks like raised or not. If in a Modal, should not be `true`

params.name: props.onPress
params.description: Function will be triggered when click the Button

name: lib/Checkbox.js
Checkbox
examples:
<Checkbox value="1" label="Checkbox On" checked={true}/>
<Checkbox value="2" label="Checkbox Off"/>
<Checkbox value="3" label="Checkbox On Disabled" checked={true} disabled={true}/>
<Checkbox value="4" label="Checkbox Off Disabled" disabled={true}/>
<Checkbox value="5" checked={true}/>
<Checkbox value="6"/>

params.name: props.label
params.description: Checkbox can have a label to describe it.

params.name: props.theme
params.description: Theme of Checkbox

params.name: props.primary
params.description: Primary color name.

params.name: props.value
params.description: Checkbox must have a value

params.name: props.checked
params.description: Specifies that an Checkbox should be pre-selected

params.name: props.disabled
params.description: Specifies that an Checkbox element should be disabled

params.name: props.onCheck
params.description:
Function will be triggered when check or
uncheck the Checkbox

name: lib/CheckboxGroup.js
CheckboxGroup
examples:
<CheckboxGroup ref="CheckboxGroup1" name="group2" onSelect={(value) => {
                           this.setState({group2Selected: value});
                       }} primary={primary}>
<Checkbox value="1" label="Checkbox On" checked={true}/>
<Checkbox value="2" label="Checkbox Off"/>
<Checkbox value="3" label="Checkbox On Disabled" checked={true} disabled={true}/>
<Checkbox value="4" label="Checkbox Off Disabled" disabled={true}/>
<Checkbox value="5" checked={true}/>
<Checkbox value="6"/>
</CheckboxGroup>
<View style={[styles.content,styles.action]}>
<Text style={{flex:1}}>Selected {this.state.group2Selected.join(',')}</Text>
<Button raised={true} value="Press to select 1,2,6" onPress={()=>{this.refs.CheckboxGroup1.value = ['1','2','6']}} />
</View>

params.name: props.name
params.description: CheckboxGroup name. Often use in form

params.name: props.theme
params.description: Checkbox theme option

params.name: props.primary
params.description: Checkbox primary color name. Specifies that which Checkbox should be pre-selected

params.name: props.value
params.description: A array save the values of checked Checkbox

params.name: props.onSelect
params.description: When CheckboxGroup value change will trigger this function

name: value
description: Get the value of checked Checkbox in CheckboxGroup. Often use in form.

name: value
description: Make CheckboxGroup set some checkbox checked

params.name: value
params.description: An array of values of some Checkbox in　CheckboxGroup

name: lib/config.js
lib/Divider.js

params.name: props.inset
params.description: Whether the divider have a 72 dp marginLeft or not
